# Vertex Workbench plugin

- Architecture and flows: `docs/ARCHITECTURE.md`
- Features, versions, fixes: `docs/FEATURES.md`
- Agent skills: `.cursor/skills/vertex-workbench-map/`, `.cursor/skills/intellij-plugin-build/`, `.cursor/skills/dual-version-maintenance/`

When changing behavior: keep two network paths separate (localhost proxy vs direct Contents HTTPS). Do not persist GCP tokens. Match existing Kotlin/IntelliJ `@Service` patterns in `dev.vertexworkbench.pycharm`.

Build: `./scripts/build-release.sh` (runs `./gradlew test buildPlugin`) / `./gradlew runIde` (Gradle 9, Java 17).

## Two build lines (always port behavior changes to both)

| Line | Root | Target IDE |
|------|------|------------|
| 2025.3.x | `/Users/oleksii/Work/pycharm-plugin` (this folder) | PyCharm Professional 2025.3.5/2025.3.6 (`sinceBuild=253`) |
| 2026.1.x | `/Users/oleksii/Work/pycharm-plugin/pycharm-plugin-2026.1` | PyCharm Professional 2026.1.2 (`sinceBuild=261`) |

Each line has its own `build.gradle.kts`, `docs/`, `src/`, `.cursor/`. When fixing a bug or adding behavior that is not Jupyter-runtime-specific, apply the same patch to both lines, run `./gradlew test` and `./scripts/build-release.sh` in each, and bump the same version number in both. See `.cursor/skills/dual-version-maintenance/SKILL.md`.

**Every version bump must also update `changeNotes` (What's New) in both `build.gradle.kts` files AND add a matching `## [0.3.N]` section to `CHANGELOG.md`.** Marketplace renders `changeNotes` as the "What's New" tab on the plugin page; skipping it ships a release with stale notes. Use HTML (`<h3>`, `<ul>`, `<li>`, `<b>`, `<code>`) — Markdown is not rendered. See the dedicated section in the dual-version-maintenance skill.
